<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-0236 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Australian Coal Association was formed in 1957. It brings togetherall groups interested in the coal industry both at national and internationallevel. It provides information to the government and the Australian publicon all industry related matters. The ACA has three members - the NewSouth Wales Coal Association, the Queensland Coal Association and theCornwall Coal Company of Tasmania. This annual report reviews the Association'sactivities over the past year.</TEXT></DOC>